episodes.title: The Red Flags of Fitness Cults | Devin But Better
episodes.description:
✨THIS WEEK✨ I am revealing major red flags that a person can bump up against when they enter a new fitness class/routine/workshop etc.

If you're new here, HI! This year we are exploring the Year of the Goddess, and with that comes a bunch unpacking the good, the bad, and the ugly experiences I've had in my quest to feel feminine, sexy, and alive. One of those experiences includes teaching and belonging to a pole dancing cult that very much still exists today - S Factor.

In this video, we are walking through the Netflix S Factor documentary, Strip Down, Rise Up together, and identifying problematic language and ideas. 

As always, I love and value respectful input - so please tell me your thoughts about this doc and video about the doc below 💃

If you liked this video, subscribe now for more: https://bit.ly/DevinButBetter

episodes.title: I Belonged to a Pole Dancing Cult (true story) | Devin But Better
episodes.description:
Hey friends! So this video feels more like a video essay, because it is. I could talk for YEARS about S Factor, pole dancing, mind body connection, the evolution of female sexuality in the mainstream, and new age manipulation, because it's so nuanced. These spaces provide a lot of good for folks. They can be healing, enlightening, and connecting. However, in the past two years I've been unpacking what was good about my experience, and when things went south, and I'd like to share my thoughts with you.

This is a ✨collective discussion✨ so feel free to chime in if you've experienced
💟 disentangling yourself from a highly controlled environment
💟 the light manipulation of a new age group
💟 curiosity around how feminine etc you are
💟 been apart of a fitness cult

I want to hear your thoughts!

If you liked this video, subscribe now for more: https://bit.ly/DevinButBetter
